Package gov.anl.ipns.ViewTools.Panels.Contour.Contours

Class Summary
Contours Encapsulates the basic information needed to use a set of contour lines needed to generate a contour plot of some data.
MixedContours Represents a collection of uniformly spaced contour levels unioned with a collection of manually specified contour levels.
NonUniformContours Represents a set of contour levels of any size and arrangement.
OrderedContours This class is used to fuse a UniformContours and NonUniformContours object together to form a set of nonuniform contour levels sorted in increasing order.
UniformContours Represents a set of uniformly spaced contour levels.
UnorderedContours Represents a collection of uniformly spaced contour lines and manually specified contour lines such that the collection is not ordered.
